51.1	Mark_Driscoll	Mark Driscoll	Mark A. Driscoll (born October 11, 1970) is an American pastor and author. He is the founder and preaching pastor of Mars Hill Church in Seattle, Washington, he co-founded the Acts 29 Network and Churches Helping Churches, and has contributed to the "Faith and Values" section of the Seattle Times and the "On Faith" section of the Washington Post. He helped start The Resurgence, a repository of missional theology resources. With his wife, he authored Real Marriage, which reached #1 on the New York Times Bestseller List in January 2012.	
